refentry.refsect1:
Description
boolw32api_deftype stringtypename stringmember1_type stringmember1_name string... string...
&warn.experimental.func;
If you would like to define a type for a w32api call, you need to call w32api_deftype. This function takes 2n+1 arguments, where n is the number of members the type has. The first argument is the name of the type. After that is the type of the member followed by the members name (in pairs). A member type can be a user defined type. &return.success;
